<p><b>Why use AutoCAD Plant 3D?</b> The AutoCAD Plant 3D toolset, included as part of the AutoCAD specialized toolset offering, help plant designers create and edit Piping & Instrumentation Diagrams (P&IDs) and to generate and modify process plant models, which they use to produce piping isometrics and piping orthographic drawings.</p>
<p><b>How do I reset a 3D plant in AutoCAD?</b> </p>
<p><b>How do you validate a 3D plant in AutoCAD?</b> There are two types of validation, one for the model alone and one for the model in relation to its associated P&ID drawing. The first is straightforward; you are simply checking for disconnected parts, placeholder parts, or property mismatches.</p>
<p><b>How do you dimension a 3D plant in AutoCAD?</b> Click Home tab Project panel Project Manager Project Setup. In the Project Setup dialog box, expand Isometric DWG Settings. Click Dimensions. On the Dimensions pane, in the Iso Style list, select the iso style for which you want to set dimensions.</p>
